description.plain:
CORPSE, also known as Corpse Husband, is an emo-styled music artist that derived from San Diego, California, who also pertains to true horror story narration series on YouTube. As of late-2020, the famous rapper garnered popularity on many platforms—especially on his YouTube channel—where he racked up over 7.5 million subscribers due to his long catalog.

To detail more on his horror story background, which dates back as early as 2015, CORPSE created consistent spooky and ominous story-telling videos that accompanied his low-pitched voice to set the mood. Over the span of those years, he was most known for that content—in his YouTube description tab featured on the channel, he attributes more on his horror video come-up:

I tell scary stories, mostly true ones, and you get scared. And I guess some people like that.

Though uncharacteristic at first, CORPSE would later upload his first gaming video on the skyrocketed video game Among Us on September 27, 2020, while also creating a designated gaming channel for future content. In the video, he collaborates with many YouTubers, with some of them being PewDiePie, jacksepticeye, Disguised Toast, LilyPichu, Sykkuno, and Valkyrae—ultimately garnering more support, a bigger audience, and a stronger pack of friends.

It’s notable to mention that some of CORPSE’s distinguishable characteristics include him having a very deep yet powerful voice, an emo-like and dark sense of music, and the palpable fact that he doesn’t truly have an identity—he’s gone to great lengths to protect showing his face to the internet. Early in 2020, on March 25 more specifically, CORPSE appeared on Anthony Padilla’s “faceless” interview session and later had an entire “I Spent a Day” episode dedicated to him, where he revealed how his secret identity comes with struggles and how it takes a toll on parts of his life.

Retrospectively, when it comes to his music, some of his famous records are “E-GIRLS ARE RUINING MY LIFE!,” “CAT GIRLS ARE RUINING MY LIFE!,” “Miss YOU!,” “White Tee,” “agoraphobic,” and “DAYWALKER!,” as they’ve all received great success, earned appropriate milestones to further CORPSE’s career, and expanded his discography.

songs.title: ​​agoraphobic

description.plain:
“agoraphobic” is CORPSE’s somber return after subsequently releasing “E-GIRLS ARE RUINING MY LIFE!,” which became a smash hit and his biggest song to date.

This song’s theme is based on the real-life condition agoraphobia, which is a panic-inducing anxiety disorder caused by the embarrassment of places and situations. CORPSE explains this is the reason he enjoys staying in isolation, due to the stigma that stems from his fame. Additionally, the sad instrumental gives the audience insight into how CORPSE’s hopelessness affects his mental state, while also pertaining to the track’s soft mood.

At first, CORPSE made it clear that this song wouldn’t be released on any streaming platform other than SoundCloud, due to him wanting to relate with core fans:

[“agoraphobic” is] only going to be on [SoundCloud] though, not iTunes or Spotify or anything like that. Just there for the people who can relate to it and want it.

Though, months later, on January 29, 2021, CORPSE ultimately decided to backtrack on his decision, and uploaded the song to all streaming platforms. A few days before the song’s official debut, CORPSE shared his reasoning via Twitter:

[I am] thinking about putting “agoraphobic” on Spotify and all that on Friday or something, everything’s fucked, might as well.
